    <description><![CDATA[
OneClick is a powerful IntelliJ IDEA plugin designed for Java developers, providing comprehensive intelligent code generation, analysis and management features.

Core Features:
- Smart One-Click Generate: Intelligently execute operations based on selected content or class type
- JavaBean Method Generation: Auto-generate getter/setter/toString/equals/hashCode methods
- DTO/VO/BO Generation: Generate data transfer objects with conversion methods
- Code Template Generator: 15 design patterns and architecture templates
- Batch Generation: Support batch processing for selected packages or files
- Refactor Assistant: 10 common refactoring operations
- Smart Comment Generation: Auto-generate comments based on code context
- Code Cleanup: Remove unused imports, empty lines, debug code, etc.
- Code Analysis: Detailed statistical analysis and quality detection
- Database Tools: Generate Entity annotations, SQL statements, Repository interfaces

Advanced Features:
- Smart Type Detection: Auto detect JavaBean vs business classes
- Configurable Package Rules: Custom package name patterns
- Field Sorting: Sort by name, length, type with modifier priority
- Customizable Shortcuts: Support different OS configurations
- Multi-language Support: Complete Chinese-English bilingual interface
- Multiple toString Styles: JSON, Simple, Apache Commons
- Fluent Setter: Support method chaining style

Quick Start:
1. Right-click in Java class and select "OneClick" menu
2. Use keyboard shortcuts (Ctrl+Shift+D / Cmd+Shift+D for smart generation)
3. Configure settings in File -> Settings -> Tools -> OneClick

For more information, please visit the project documentation.
    ]]></description>

